   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Copy of agreement. Year 13 &lt;or 16&gt; of the Emperor Caesar Nerva [Trajan] Augustus Germanicus Dacicus, month Sebastos 25, in Ptolemais Euergetis of the Arsinoite nome. Pakysis, son of Petenouphis, Persian of the epigone, about 20 years old, with a scar on his left forearm, acknowledges to Tattion(?), daughter of Saturnilus, about 35 years old, with a scar on her left knee, having as her guardian her kinsman Sotas, son of Petenouris, about 40 years old, with a scar on his right knee, that he has received from her herewith in cash four hundred drachmai in silver . . . [- - - ].</ab>
         </div>
